tips.text: Unpretentious yes. Ambience is a word thrown about by many who cannot fathom its meaning. No ambience hence unpretentious... ta-dah! Expect your uni  co-op coffeeshop, & then take it down a notch.

tips.text: Those china worker attitude is dam fuck up!

Only come after 1130am if you're hoping to buy the ondeh ondeh. Parking is challenging here on the weekends.

Raw Fish Slices are cheap and to die for after a hard days work.

Dumplings and gyoza. Fried spicy chicken

formattedAddress: 32 New Market St (Eu Tong Sen St)

tips.text: Yong tau foo: Lots of stalls here. 1 of them, Poy Kee Yong Tau Foo #01-1066, sees daily loyals. Fishball salty but everything else is yummy. Noodles q, chilli sauce kicking!
Duck confit was the best we've had in Singapore. Crispy & fragrant, every bite was pleasurable. And there's that sinful side of potato crisp fried in duck fat. Ahhh...

tips.text: Now they offer free ramen set if you visit on your actual birthday! The staff is very cool about this too. Visit passp.asia for more japanese food deals!

tips.text: This bakuteh version contains  當归 herb which I like. But pepper fans beware that there is almost no pepper taste in the soup. 煮炒is good. Try their prawn paste chicken. #ThomtoriEats #bakuteh
Every single thing we ordered was superb. Reasonably price too
Half baked chocolate cake is a must try. Large size main course steak is enough for two to share.

tips.text: almond paste is nice... good for lungs and skin   ;-)
Try the Luna cakes! They're like mini pancakes wrapped around cream and fillings. Very soft and yummy. Mostly a take away place, they do have 2 tiny tables outside along the corridor though.
Nope. Never again.
Bak Kwa! Minced Pork & Sliced Pork are delicious!
Just order anything.
This is one of the best kept secrets in Singapore, they have a great champagne selection and one the best cold cuts and cheese platters in town.
Paris-born chef Frederic Colin’s re-imagination of early 1900s Parisian coffeehouses – a quaint, Art Nouveau-style space filled with rattan chairs, cobblestone floors and elegant tiled paintings...
Good food and really great service. I miss them already!
Wonderful, comfort food. Really like the bakwan kepeting and the ayam buah keluak.

order the northern stuff, obviously - good homestyle cooking. 地三鮮，醬茄子，酸菜粉絲，涼拌腐皮絲，東北拉皮 are all excellent and filling.

Délicieux fruits de mer dont le fameux "black pepper crab" à déguster avec des legumes et du riz. Ou le steamed crab. La carte est riche, accueil sympa. Compter 58$ le kilo. Bon vin 45$/bouteille.

By the same people behind Binomio next door. Unfortunately don't expect the same standard. Tapas are ok but portions for main are tiny! Oxtail sandwich worth a try but avoid the forgettable pork ribs.
Great service, ask for a selection of what they think is best and you won't be disappointed.
From kaiseiki, they have changed to a la carte japanese restaurant. Quality of food is still stand out. Sashimi platter was pure joy to eat, grilled onigiri had homemade taste & somen was refreshing.
Just tried the crème caramel maison and the dame blanche, it was yummy ! (Tested and approved by a genuine French girl !)

tips.text: Humongous portions of tendon for special set (chicken, prawn, etc). Highlight def is fried onsen egg. Break the yolk over rice for instant heaven! The washroom has heated toilet seat cover & bidet.

tips.text: Basically everything here is good. Must try their homemade tofu and porridge. Claypot frog leg is also recommended! 😍 love this place
